source:
TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_SEQ_00<tab><var 48 F201FC /var><var 49 F201FD /var> Quest Sync<var 49 01 /var><var 48 01 /var>
Ghun Gun is finally ready to obey his father's orders to take a well-earned rest.
target:
TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_SEQ_00<tab><var 48 F201FC /var><var 49 F201FD /var>Règle spéciale<var 1D /var>:  synchronisation de quête<var 49 01 /var><var 48 01 /var>
Ghun Gun a la ferme intention de finalement se reposer.

source:
TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_SEQ_01<tab>Ghun Gun's idea of a rest appears to involve listening intently to Jamial propose an expedition in search of buried treasure. The aged historian believes that a trail of discarded relics left behind when the Nabaath fled the Flood of Light is waiting to be discovered, and asks you and Ghun Gun to help him with its excavation. Satisfied that standing still for a few moments constitutes rest and recuperation, your Mord companion springs into action, practically salivating at the chance to go digging for more priceless artifacts.

※Please note that the difficulty of this quest has been synced to your current level.
target:
TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_SEQ_01<tab><var 1A 02 /var>Cette quête est <var 48 F201FC /var><var 49 F201FD /var> synchronisée<var 49 01 /var><var 48 01 /var> avec votre niveau.<var 1A 01 /var>

Jamial a profité de la pause bien méritée de Ghun Gun pour lui demander de l'aider à trouver d'autres reliques de Nabaath Areng. Vous avez décidé de mettre la main à la pâte également, allez rejoindre Jamial à l'auberge du Grand Départ.

source: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_SEQ_02<tab>Jamial leads you to a stretch of desert near the Inn at Journey's Head, where Ghun Gun immediately throws himself into the search for buried relics. While you set about the task at hand, Jamial, far too old for such demanding physical exertion, watches on.
target: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_SEQ_02<tab>Jamial vous a appris que ce que vous cherchiez était dissimulé non loin de l'auberge du Grand Départ. Allez fouiller à l'endroit indiqué.

source: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_SEQ_03<tab>Your search reveals a large shield of some description, although it is hard to see what lies below layer upon layer of grime. Ghun Gun, however, is accustomed to removing this sort of caked-on dirt with little more than his hands, so you take it to him to have it cleaned for inspection.
target: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_SEQ_03<tab>Vous avez fait une découverte intéressante. Allez la montrer à Ghun Gun.

source: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_SEQ_04<tab>The artifact you have unearthed is a heraldic shield which, according to Jamial, represents the great houses of Nabaath Areng. He also explains that the Mord were an intrinsic part of the nation's rise to greatness, much to the surprise of Ghun Gun. Jamial then sets his sights on the next location, between an enormous section of ruined wall and a decidedly precarious precipice.
target: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_SEQ_04<tab>Jamial vous a raconté l'histoire de la con<var 16 /var>struc<var 16 /var>tion de Nabaath Areng, et vous a demandé de le suivre à La Guette, pour continuer à chercher d'autres reliques.

source: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_SEQ_05<tab>Upon arrival, Jamial directs you and Ghun Gun to a large pile of debris that seems to have crumbled away from the nearby ruins. Once again, you set to work, hoping to find remnants of the Nabaath's past.
target: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_SEQ_05<tab>Allez creuser à l'endoit indiqué.

source: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_SEQ_06<tab>Your search bears fruit, although exactly what kind of fruit, you cannot be sure. You wisely choose to leave the delicate task of brushing away the encrusted soil to Ghun Gun, who is still busy sifting through the rubble.
target: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_SEQ_06<tab>Vous avez trouvé une statuette cassée. Allez la faire examiner par Ghun Gun.

source: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_SEQ_07<tab>Ghun Gun takes great delight in explaining that the relic is in fact an example of traditional Mord craftsmanship, though the small statue seems to be little more than a round ball of clay with holes bored into it. Jamial posits that it once took pride of place in the Pristine Palace of Amh Malik as a symbol of the friendship between the Nabaath and the Mord. Although there is still one more site that he would like to investigate, Jamial takes this opportunity to offer his gratitude for your sterling work thus far.
target: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_SEQ_07<tab>Après avoir jeté un œil à la statuette, Jamial vous a expliqué que les Mords et les Humes entretenaient une relation amicale, malgré des débuts tumultueux. Il reste une dernière étape à la visite du vieil antiquaire, suivez-le et continuez à aider vos deux comparses.

source: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_JAMIAL_000_000<tab>Perhaps this would be a good opportunity...
target: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_JAMIAL_000_000<tab>Maintenant que tu as trouvé ce sceau, je pense que je peux me lancer à la recherche d'autres reliques...

source: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_GHUNGUN_000_010<tab>Now that business with the ring is over, I should rest, as I said I would. Then your promise to my father will be fulfilled!
target: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_GHUNGUN_000_010<tab>Je pense qu'il est temps que je tienne ma promesse, oui<var 1D /var>! Je vais de ce pas prendre une petite pause bien méritée<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_JAMIAL_000_011<tab>Actually, there is something I should like to discuss with you. I am in no rush, however, so let us speak again after your repose.
target: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_JAMIAL_000_011<tab>Tu, euh.. Tu pourrais revenir me voir après ta pause<var 1D /var>? Je voudrais vous demander quelque chose, à tous les deux...

source: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_GHUNGUN_000_012<tab>Ah! My curiosity! It is piqued! Please, you must tell me now! I can rest while I listen.
target: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_GHUNGUN_000_012<tab>Bien sûr<var 1D /var>! Tu sais quoi, je vais même t'écouter pendant ma pause, ici et maintenant, oui oui<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_JAMIAL_000_013<tab>Oh... Well, if you insist.
target: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_JAMIAL_000_013<tab>T'es sûr<var 1D /var>? Bon alors dans ce cas...

source: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_JAMIAL_000_014<tab>I would like you to help me search for more relics from Nabaath Areng. If my suppositions are correct, I know where many such artifacts are waiting to be uncovered.
target: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_JAMIAL_000_014<tab>Ma requête est simple, j'aimerais que vous m'aidiez à trouver d'autres reliques de Nabaath Areng. Je suis certain que le sceau que vous avez dégoté ne s'est pas retrouvé là par hasard... Il doit y avoir d'autres objets similaires dans les parages<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_JAMIAL_000_015<tab>I base this claim on my knowledge of the route chosen by the malik when he led his people's exodus from the Flood of Light.
target: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_JAMIAL_000_015<tab>Juste avant que le déluge de Lumière ne détruise la capitale impériale, le dernier souverain de Nabaath Areng a fui le royaume, emmenant avec lui son jeune fils et son peuple.

source: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_JAMIAL_000_016<tab>Although many tried to take their most prized possessions with them, it soon became apparent that such burdens would only hinder their escape. Each household discarded their personal treasures, one piece at a time.
target: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_JAMIAL_000_016<tab>Les sujets du royaume ont d'abord tenté d'emporter avec eux le plus de richesses possible, mais ils ont dû les abandonner en route pour faciliter leur fuite.

source: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_JAMIAL_000_017<tab>By following the exact path traveled from Nabaath Areng, we would be able to unearth many more priceless treasures. What say you? Will you lend me your aid?
target: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_JAMIAL_000_017<tab>Ces trésors n'ont jamais été retrouvés... Mais la découverte de ce sceau change la donne, car maintenant nous avons une indication précise de la zone où chercher<var 1D /var>! Que diriez-vous de procéder aux fouilles avec moi<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_GHUNGUN_000_018<tab>Of course! And now that I have finished resting, I am ready to start digging!
target: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_GHUNGUN_000_018<tab>Avec plaisir<var 1D /var>! Je suis complétement requinqué après cette pause, requinqué, oui<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_JAMIAL_000_019<tab>You are quite sure?
target: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_JAMIAL_000_019<tab>Ça veut dire que tu acceptes<var 1D /var>? Parfait<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_GHUNGUN_000_020<tab>I am! <var 2C ((<var 29 EB02 /var>)) (( )) 02 /var>, you should come too! You have already found one of these shinies. Maybe you can find some more!
target: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_GHUNGUN_000_020<tab>Tu viens avec nous, <var 2C ((<var 29 EB02 /var>)) (( )) 02 /var>, oui<var 1D /var>? C'est toi qui as trouvé le sceau, tu as droit à ta part du trésor<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_JAMIAL_000_021<tab>You will be amply remunerated for your efforts even if there are no profits to be made from the sale of the items themselves. I too am a proponent of the motto “Honest pay for honest work.”
target: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_JAMIAL_000_021<tab>Même si nous ne trouvons que des objets de faible valeur, je promets de te récompenser à la hauteur de tes efforts<var 1D /var>! Qu'en dis-tu<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_GHUNGUN_000_022<tab>We should go before my father tries to stop me! Honestly, there is no such thing as working too hard! Oh, wait... Where are we going?
target: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_GHUNGUN_000_022<tab>C'est parti<var 1D /var>! Dépêchons-nous avant que mon paternel ne vienne encore jouer les rabat-joie<var 1D /var>! Euh, par contre je sais pas où il faut aller, non non<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_JAMIAL_000_023<tab>The first location is to the east of the Inn at Journey's Head. Allow me to lead the way!
target: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_JAMIAL_000_023<tab>Commençons par aller inspecter à l'est de l'auberge du Grand Départ.

source: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_GHUNGUN_000_030<tab>It does not smell of treasure here. Maybe I am not sniffing hard enough?
target: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_GHUNGUN_000_030<tab>Le travail est pour les Mords un trésor, oui oui<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_JAMIAL_000_040<tab>As I recall, there should be a few artifacts scattered around this area.
target: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_JAMIAL_000_040<tab>Tu as fait vite<var 1D /var>! Nous y voilà, c'est donc ici que les habitants de Nabaath Areng en fuite ont jeté leurs possessions.

source: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_JAMIAL_000_041<tab>The first items to be discarded were those of little value or simply too cumbersome to be carried over long distances. However, we can assume that many were buried so that they could be recovered later.
target: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_JAMIAL_000_041<tab>Ils ont pro<var 16 /var>ba<var 16 /var>ble<var 16 /var>ment commencé par se débarasser des objets de moindre valeur, mais avaient dans l'idée de venir les récupérer plus tard. J'imagine qu'ils ont pris le temps de tout dissimuler...

source: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_JAMIAL_000_042<tab>Therefore, it seems logical that landmarks such as large outcrops and so forth would be used to indicate their position.
target: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_JAMIAL_000_042<tab>Je suis sûr que c'est par ici. Ils ont forcément choisi des endroits faciles à retrouver.

source: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_GHUNGUN_000_043<tab>Less talking, more digging! I want to find the shinies!
target: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_GHUNGUN_000_043<tab>Dans ce cas, il est temps de creuser, oui oui<var 1D /var>! Toi aussi, <var 2C ((<var 29 EB02 /var>)) (( )) 02 /var><var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_JAMIAL_000_050<tab>As much as I would like to assist in the search, I am afraid that these old bones of mine make bending and kneeling quite a struggle.
target: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_JAMIAL_000_050<tab>J'aimerais pouvoir creuser avec vous, mais avec mes vieux os... Je vous gênerais plus qu'autre chose...

source: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_JAMIAL_000_060<tab>Have you found something? Perhaps you could get Ghun Gun to clean off some of the dirt. Mord hands are perfectly suited to that sort of delicate work.
target: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_JAMIAL_000_060<tab>Oh oh, tu as découvert quelque chose<var 1D /var>? Commence par aller montrer ta trouvaille à Ghun Gun<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_GHUNGUN_000_070<tab>Mmm... Lots of lovely shinies over here! What have you got?
target: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_GHUNGUN_000_070<tab>J'ai trouvé quelques babioles de mon côté, des babioles, oui. Et toi<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_GHUNGUN_000_071<tab>Oh, a great big shiny! Is this...a dinner plate?
target: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_GHUNGUN_000_071<tab>Oh<var 1D /var>!! C'est superbe<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_GHUNGUN_000_072<tab>Jamial, what is this?
target: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_GHUNGUN_000_072<tab>Dis, Jamial, tu saurais nous dire ce que c'est, oui<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_JAMIAL_000_073<tab>A heraldic shield. The five coins above a castle represent each of the great houses of Nabaath Areng.
target: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_JAMIAL_000_073<tab>C'est un bouclier qui porte les armoiries de Nabaath Areng. Les cinq pièces que vous voyez autour du château re<var 16 /var>pré<var 16 /var>sen<var 16 /var>tent les cinq tribus du royaume.

source: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_GHUNGUN_000_074<tab>Coins? Is that because they were rich?
target: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_GHUNGUN_000_074<tab>Oooh, Nabaath Areng devait être un royaume très prospère, oui<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_JAMIAL_000_075<tab>Precisely. The capital attracted trade from across Norvrandt, and much of the wealth found its way into their coffers.
target: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_JAMIAL_000_075<tab>Bien sûr, c'était le plus grand carrefour de commerce de la région, et on y trouvait toutes les plus somptueuses richesses de Norvrandt.

source: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_JAMIAL_000_076<tab>Such a booming economy was not built overnight, however. Although Nabaath Areng was largely established by Humes, the harsh desert environment meant that they had to rely on the aid of neighboring peoples.
target: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_JAMIAL_000_076<tab>Vous saviez que ce royaume avait été contruit par les Humes<var 1D /var>? Une grande partie de la région étant désertique, la pauvreté était rampante à cette époque.

source: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_JAMIAL_000_077<tab>It was the Mord who taught them how to safely traverse the barren plains, methods for finding sustenance, and much besides. They were also respected partners in matters of commerce. The Nabaath owed a great deal to your ancestors, Ghun Gun.
target: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_JAMIAL_000_077<tab>Jusqu'à ce que les Mords arrivent et leur apprennent à vivre dans le désert. Grâce à leurs con<var 16 /var>nais<var 16 /var>san<var 16 /var>ces, Nabaath Areng devint rapidement une contrée prospère, aux routes commerciales florissantes. C'est grâce à eux que nous nous souvenons de la gloire de ce royaume encore aujourd'hui.

source: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_GHUNGUN_000_078<tab>I...never knew.
target: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_GHUNGUN_000_078<tab>Je ne connaissais pas cette histoire, non non...

source: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_JAMIAL_000_079<tab>History is all around us, if we know where to look. Which reminds me, the next location I would like to search is not far from here. This way, if you please.
target: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_JAMIAL_000_079<tab>Assez traîné, dirigeons-nous vers le deuxième site de fouilles. C'est un peu plus au sud.

source: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_GHUNGUN_000_080<tab>Do you think there will be more shinies?
target: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_GHUNGUN_000_080<tab>J'espère qu'on va trouver plein de trésors ici, plein de trésors, oui<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_JAMIAL_000_090<tab>I have reason to believe that more artifacts are resting beneath these ruins. Please take the utmost care with any that you discover, as some may be fragile.
target: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_JAMIAL_000_090<tab>Nous y sommes<var 1D /var>! Je sens qu'il y a quelque chose sous ces débris. À vous de jouer<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_JAMIAL_100_090<tab>Should you find any remnants of the past, I would be very glad to see them, no matter how inconsequential they may seem.
target: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_JAMIAL_100_090<tab>Je sens qu'il y a quelque chose sous ces débris. À vous de jouer<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_JAMIAL_000_100<tab>Excellent work! Once Ghun Gun has cleaned off the excess grime, we can verify whether this relic has any historical importance.
target: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_JAMIAL_000_100<tab>Oh, tu as encore trouvé une relique<var 1D /var>? Va vite montrer ça à Ghun Gun.

source: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_GHUNGUN_000_110<tab>Nothing but bricks and sand. Have you had better luck?
target: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_GHUNGUN_000_110<tab>J'ai rien trouvé, rien trouvé du tout, non<var 1D /var>! J'espère que tu as eu plus de chance que moi<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_GHUNGUN_000_111<tab>I know what this is! A decorative Mord's head sculpture! Making these is one of our many traditions!
target: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_GHUNGUN_000_111<tab>C'est une statuette morde... Mais elle est dans un très mauvais état, très mauvais oui<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_GHUNGUN_000_112<tab>But what is it doing here?
target: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_GHUNGUN_000_112<tab>Jamial, tu peux jeter un œil à ce que <var 2C ((<var 29 EB02 /var>)) (( )) 02 /var> a trouvé, oui<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_JAMIAL_000_113<tab>We may surmise that it was once kept in the Pristine Palace of Amh Malik. It once housed tokens of friendship from allied peoples. That the malik brought such gifts so far from Nabaath Areng is proof of their cultural significance.
target: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_JAMIAL_000_113<tab>C'était pro<var 16 /var>ba<var 16 /var>ble<var 16 /var>ment une ornementation du palais d'Amh Malik<var 1D /var>! Il y avait beaucoup de statuettes mordes dans le palais, preuve de l'amitié entre les deux peuples.

source: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_JAMIAL_000_114<tab>However, when the Nabaath and the Mord first came into contact, there were many disagreements.
target: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_JAMIAL_000_114<tab>Cependant, les Mords et les Humes n'ont pas toujours eu cette relation amicale, vous savez. Au tout début, les deux peuples étaient même en guerre<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_GHUNGUN_000_115<tab>Hmm? I do not understand. We Mord hate arguing! The art of negotiation is another one of our many traditions!
target: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_GHUNGUN_000_115<tab>C'est vrai<var 1D /var>? C'est difficile à croire, très difficile, oui oui<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_JAMIAL_000_116<tab>Yes, I daresay that was a decisive factor in these disparate peoples finding common ground. And yet the Mord live on while the Nabaath are no more.
target: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_JAMIAL_000_116<tab>Leur alliance est le résultat de longues années de négociation et d'efforts des deux côtés... Dont nous continuons de bénéficier encore aujourd'hui.

source: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_JAMIAL_000_117<tab>Hopefully, we will uncover yet more valuable insights to the past at our final excavation site. And may I say, your work thus far has been nothing short of exemplary.
target: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_JAMIAL_000_117<tab>Merci de m'avoir accompagné jusqu'ici. Il reste un dernier endroit où je voudrais que vous cherchiez.

source: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_GHUNGUN_000_118<tab>Please, save your thanks for when we have finished!
target: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_GHUNGUN_000_118<tab>C'est trop tôt pour les re<var 16 /var>mer<var 16 /var>cie<var 16 /var>ments, oui<var 1D /var>! Garde-les pour quand on aura trouvé le dernier trésor<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_GHUNGUN_000_119<tab>There is much still to be done, more treasures to be found!
target: TEXT_LUCKZA203_03377_GHUNGUN_000_119<tab>Dépêchons-nous de nous y rendre, <var 2C ((<var 29 EB02 /var>)) (( )) 02 /var><var 1D /var>! J'ai hâte de me remettre au travail, très hâte, oui oui<var 1D /var>!
